Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.23,0:00:28.29,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(357,126)\fad(1600,1006)}And I stood upon the sand of the sea, and saw a Monster rise up out of the sea,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.27,0:00:28.29,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(352,163)\fad(1100,1031)}having seven heads and ten horns, and upon his horns ten crowns,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.19,0:00:28.29,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(356,202)\fad(1000,1010)}And upon his head the name of blasphemy (...)
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.19,0:00:28.29,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(356,238)\fad(1000,710)}And they worshiped the dragon which gave power unto the Monster:
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.20,0:00:28.29,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(356,276)\fad(1000,409)}and they worshiped the Monster, saying,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.20,0:00:28.29,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(346,314)\fad(1000,109)}"Who is like unto the Monster?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.20,0:00:28.29,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(356,355)\fad(600,209)}Who is able to make war with him?"
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.37,0:00:28.29,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(352,454)\fad(350,142)}< The Black Book of Johann, Revelation 13, #1-4 > \N This is an actual passage from the Bible with the word \N "beast" replaced with "monster," and "Ioanes" with "Johann."
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.82,0:00:38.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That was amazing!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.07,0:00:40.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, his skills are unmatched
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.53,0:00:44.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I couldn't believe his speed, even when clipping \N that difficult cranial arterial mass!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.99,0:00:45.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.95,0:00:48.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That was a splendid operation, Herr Dr. Tenma.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.29,0:00:53.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I finally got to see what a genius Kenzou \N Tenma is with my own eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.96,0:00:56.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, it was all due to everyone's hard work.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.38,0:00:57.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you very much.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.59,0:01:00.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't believe the sun is so high already...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.92,0:01:04.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, we did operate for six hours straight.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.60,0:01:08.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There aren't any other patients today, so rest up.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.96,0:01:39.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, where is daddy?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.12,0:01:41.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What happened to daddy?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.51,0:03:25.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(363,330)\fad(396)}Herr Dr. Tenma
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.47,0:03:30.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(367,384)\fad(300,142)}Düsseldorf \N (Germany)
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.02,0:03:53.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come on, wake up already.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.19,0:03:55.40,Stuff,,0000,0000,0000,,Good morning.  This is the news at eight.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.11,0:03:55.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wake up, Dr. Tenma.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.50,0:03:58.92,Stuff,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(366,359)\fad(200,142)}Kenzou Tenma
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.40,0:03:58.69,Stuff,,0000,0000,0000,,We're here to bring you the following news.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.53,0:04:03.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't you think the roles have been reversed?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.01,0:04:05.37,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(377,387)\fad(200,136)}Eva Heinemann
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.70,0:04:07.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It should be a princess like myself being woken with a kiss.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.12,0:04:10.12,Stuff,,0000,0000,0000,,First, the widespread news about the East German \N Foreign Trade Adviser, Mr. Liebert.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.37,0:04:10.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, you are here, Eva?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.12,0:04:12.08,Stuff,,0000,0000,0000,,Hello, Mr. Reimann from Düsseldorf.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.08,0:04:15.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You forgot about our date, didn't you, Kenzou?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.33,0:04:15.67,Stuff,,0000,0000,0000,,We're here in Düsseldorf.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.88,0:04:18.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, it's not that I forgot about it...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.83,0:04:21.42,Stuff,,0000,0000,0000,,Now that the Foreign Trade Adviser who fled to West Germany...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.42,0:04:27.30,Stuff,,0000,0000,0000,,Adviser Liebert made an appearance before the media with his family yesterday.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.55,0:04:30.01,Stuff,,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Liebert, without any sign of fatigue on his face...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.01,0:04:33.43,Stuff,,0000,0000,0000,,...along with his twin son and daughter...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.43,0:04:36.10,Stuff,,0000,0000,0000,,...appeared, smiling brightly.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.10,0:04:40.44,Stuff,,0000,0000,0000,,His family is planning to stay here in Düsseldorf for some time...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.44,0:04:43.73,Stuff,,0000,0000,0000,,...and carry on with their daily lives in an apartment provided by our TV station.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.11,0:04:46.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't feel like I've slept at all...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.15,0:04:47.03,Stuff,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, onto the next story.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.74,0:04:50.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, wake up!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.11,0:04:51.95,Stuff,,0000,0000,0000,,The famous opera singer, Mr. Rosenbach...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.65,0:04:51.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This one is about you!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.95,0:04:54.57,Stuff,,0000,0000,0000,,...collapsed yesterday due to an internal hemorrhage.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.57,0:04:57.37,Stuff,,0000,0000,0000,,He is reported to be in stable condition after surgery.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.37,0:05:01.33,Stuff,,0000,0000,0000,,Director Heinemann, from the Düsseldorf Eisler Memorial \N Hospital, participated in the operation...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.33,0:05:04.29,Stuff,,0000,0000,0000,,...and held a press conference a short time ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.50,0:05:08.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Rosenbach's diagnosis revealed that he suffered \N from a ruptured artery in the brain.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.92,0:05:11.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The operation itself went accordingly.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.17,0:05:15.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The clipping went extremely well, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.80,0:05:18.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Rosenbach has numerous fans.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.55,0:05:19.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you think he'll make a full recovery?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.18,0:05:25.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, we'll put forth every effort \N to recover his singing voice.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.64,0:05:31.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dr. Heinemann's team has had success in \N numerous difficult operations to date.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.48,0:05:37.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But with this operation, we can now say that they have \N secured their position in the medical world in our country.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.86,0:05:40.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That is amazing, Kenzou!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.03,0:05:41.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The news wasn't about me...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.86,0:05:43.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was about your father.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.70,0:05:45.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That is true, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.41,0:05:51.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's because you performed a perfect surgery \N with my father's team last night.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.29,0:05:51.25,Stuff,,0000,0000,0000,,In other news...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.25,0:05:53.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure father appreciates your efforts.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.46,0:05:56.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're responsible for improving the hospital's reputation.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.29,0:05:59.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm the one who should be thankful...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.71,0:06:04.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...since it's thanks to your father that \N I can work like this in Germany.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.68,0:06:06.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Good luck, Kenzou.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.59,0:06:09.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm positive everything will work out fine \N if you follow in my father's footsteps.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.60,0:06:13.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's only matter of time before my father becomes the chief director.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.18,0:06:15.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then you'll soon be the head of the surgical department.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.98,0:06:18.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And eventually, a director.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.60,0:06:22.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That'll make me the wife of a director.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.36,0:06:23.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You better make me happy...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.98,0:06:26.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...because hardship doesn't suit me.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.24,0:06:28.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Should we leave?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.82,0:06:30.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Or should we...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.86,0:06:36.12,Stuff,,0000,0000,0000,,...the southern region will be rainy over the weekend.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.29,0:06:41.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Blood pressure, 128/64.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.96,0:06:42.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Retractor.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.92,0:06:48.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going to make an incision in the pyramis now.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.13,0:06:58.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That was a perfect operation as usual, Dr. Tenma!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.76,0:07:00.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you very much.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.44,0:07:03.02,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(366,386)\fad(150,108)}Dr. Becker
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.43,0:07:03.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Although it doesn't seem like you're \N only good at operating on people...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.48,0:07:07.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You hold the position of chief at such a young age...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.98,0:07:10.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...and both the director and the surgical head hold you in the high esteem.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.40,0:07:11.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And on top of that...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.69,0:07:15.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...you won the heart of the director's daughter.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.23,0:07:18.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you trying to say, Dr. Becker?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.45,0:07:22.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry.  I don't mean anything bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.24,0:07:24.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Because a hospital is just a world of politics.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.58,0:07:29.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You know full well that you're being \N used by the director, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.96,0:07:32.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The operation that you performed \N successfully on the opera singer...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.96,0:07:37.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He held a press conference on TV \N as if he did everything himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.34,0:07:42.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Although it means you have talent, if you're being used.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.63,0:07:45.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When you get promoted, put in a good word for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.34,0:07:48.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll treat you sometime, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.07,0:08:14.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Umm, may I help you?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.45,0:08:16.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're Dr. Tenma?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.62,0:08:17.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.50,0:08:20.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Give me back my husband.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.42,0:08:25.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Give him back!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.75,0:08:30.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why didn't you operate on my husband?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.09,0:08:31.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Y-You are...?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.51,0:08:35.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My husband was brought into the hospital first!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.39,0:08:38.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He was brought in long before that stupid opera singer!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.85,0:08:41.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But you guys pushed him back!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.64,0:08:46.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Aren't you the most skilled doctor in this hospital?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.02,0:08:47.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So why?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.27,0:08:50.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.90,0:08:53.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was then I recalled that....
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.11,0:08:59.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was going to operate on a Turkish man who \N got injured in a construction accident.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.91,0:09:01.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dr. Tenma!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.57,0:09:02.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.82,0:09:04.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This isn't your operation.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.37,0:09:06.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hurry up and go to operating room #1.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.37,0:09:09.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's an order from the director.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.33,0:09:10.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please hurry!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.42,0:09:15.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If only you had operated on him, \N he would have survived!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.63,0:09:16.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If only you had...!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.42,0:09:18.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mom!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.21,0:09:20.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Give him back!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.05,0:09:21.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Give him back...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.71,0:09:22.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mom!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.39,0:09:29.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So my friend and I fought over that dress.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.89,0:09:31.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They only had one dress of that size left.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.18,0:09:33.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But you don't have to worry about anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.48,0:09:35.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I made it mine in the end.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.89,0:09:38.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, are you listening to me?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.15,0:09:42.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.52,0:09:44.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is wrong with you?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.11,0:09:45.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You seem out of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.78,0:09:47.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I checked the medical records...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.74,0:09:51.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The one who operated on the \N Turkish man was Dr. Becker.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.82,0:09:54.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, come on.  You're still talking about that?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.08,0:09:57.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's obvious that he took too much \N time to begin the treatment.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.54,0:10:00.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If I were the one who had operated on him...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.00,0:10:04.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...maybe I could have saved that Turkish man's life.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.84,0:10:06.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Stop it!  We're eating here!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.84,0:10:09.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But what does she want from me?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.55,0:10:14.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I only operated on the opera singer because \N the director ordered me to.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.18,0:10:15.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not my fault.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.09,0:10:17.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't you think so?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.18,0:10:20.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.02,0:10:24.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Because people's lives aren't equal.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.95,0:10:43.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Give him back!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.87,0:10:45.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Give my husband back!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.95,0:10:47.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Give him back!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.80,0:11:01.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is that the house?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.88,0:11:04.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, the report was made by one of the neighbors.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.47,0:11:08.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How many shots were fired?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.18,0:11:09.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Five or six, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.56,0:11:10.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who lives in this house?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.22,0:11:12.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,W-Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.81,0:11:17.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's the house of Mr. Liebert, the trade adviser \N who fled from East Germany a few days ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.56,0:11:21.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, this is going to be a problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.36,0:11:29.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're going in on the count or three.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.24,0:11:30.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,One...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.24,0:11:31.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Two...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.07,0:11:31.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Three!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.22,0:11:56.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is terrible...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.64,0:11:58.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who could have...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.68,0:12:03.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,S-Someone is there!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.95,0:12:21.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Survivor confirmed.  One young girl.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.91,0:12:23.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A man and a woman are dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.41,0:12:25.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A boy in critical condition.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.37,0:12:26.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I repeat...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.45,0:12:28.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A boy in critical condition!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.67,0:12:41.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,An emergency case?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.27,0:12:48.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A bullet in his head?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.28,0:12:51.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The boy is the only patient?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.53,0:12:53.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, his parents died instantly.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.70,0:12:55.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It appears to be a robbery of some kind.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.16,0:12:59.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, I'll be at the hospital in about five minutes.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.88,0:13:10.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, father.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.17,0:13:16.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please forgive me, Dr. Heinemann, for \N keeping your daughter out so late.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.46,0:13:18.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you saying, Tenma?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.72,0:13:21.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Eva is your fiancé, isn't she?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.76,0:13:22.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you say?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.89,0:13:25.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Would you like to have a cup of tea?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.43,0:13:31.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Have you given the wedding \N date to your parents in Japan?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.85,0:13:33.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Y-Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.44,0:13:37.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But my father is only a practitioner in a small hospital...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.15,0:13:40.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...so I'm not sure if he can make \N time to come to Germany.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.48,0:13:45.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's perfect opportunity, so they\N should enjoy an overseas trip.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.91,0:13:48.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, since we're the ones who invited them.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.53,0:13:51.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you very much.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.33,0:13:54.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm indebted to you for everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.83,0:13:56.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When you first arrived in Germany...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.87,0:13:59.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...I thought you were just some high school kid.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.84,0:14:04.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But now, you're the number one young surgeon of Eisler Memorial.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.84,0:14:07.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,By the way, Kenzou...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.63,0:14:13.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your current research into cerebral ischemia \N and subarachnoid hemorrhages...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.39,0:14:17.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, we're currently making a canine model \N of the subarachnoid hemorrhages.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.64,0:14:20.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry, but that research has to be canceled.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.85,0:14:21.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.48,0:14:29.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In the upcoming European Medical Science Symposium, \N I am making a presentation as a speaker.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.23,0:14:32.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I want you to prepare the manuscripts for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.15,0:14:37.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But... we're near the completion of our research.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.78,0:14:41.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Man, you should have been there this afternoon.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.08,0:14:43.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What happened father?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.16,0:14:47.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Some suspicious civilian group \N came rushing into the hospital.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.12,0:14:50.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They made a commotion about the operation we \N performed on the opera singer the other day.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.88,0:14:55.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They accused us of pushing back the case \N of the Turkish man that came before him.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.97,0:14:59.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They completely misunderstood the situation.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.09,0:15:02.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Turkish man's operation was performed first.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.55,0:15:06.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There was nothing wrong with our procedures.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.89,0:15:10.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't that right?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.31,0:15:13.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,S-Sure...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.77,0:15:18.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I swear, they think doctors are some kind of volunteers or something.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.32,0:15:22.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even before saving lives, we doctors value academics first.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.36,0:15:23.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't that right?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.16,0:15:30.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In any case, I'll leave the manuscripts \N for my presentation to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.79,0:15:34.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I expect a great deal from you, Tenma.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.46,0:15:38.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.35,0:15:56.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shit!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.07,0:16:08.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Where is the patient?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.91,0:16:10.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They have taken him inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.54,0:16:14.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is his condition?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.50,0:16:16.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Blood pressure, 72/50
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.83,0:16:18.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Pulse, 137.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.87,0:16:21.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So the bullet entered his skull from the front...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.71,0:16:23.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We need X-Rays immediately!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.13,0:16:24.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.59,0:16:28.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, Dr. Tenma!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.01,0:16:34.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who is this girl?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.05,0:16:36.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She is the twin sister of that boy just now.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.93,0:16:37.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Any injuries?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.89,0:16:39.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,None.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.02,0:16:41.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It appears she suffered a massive mental shock.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.48,0:16:48.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.40,0:16:50.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kill. Him.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.95,0:16:58.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dr. Tenma!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.58,0:17:02.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Head shots and CT scans are ready.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.70,0:17:04.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, I'll be right there.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.12,0:17:09.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It entered the head from the front, and embedded itself near the center of the brain.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.33,0:17:11.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.75,0:17:13.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This will be difficult.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.30,0:17:18.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The bullet grazed the left side \N of the middle cerebral artery.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.63,0:17:23.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see.  Dr. Tenma is right!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.26,0:17:25.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This won't be easy.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.22,0:17:27.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If we move the bullet even a little...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.52,0:17:30.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...it might rupture and cause a massive hemorrhage.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.77,0:17:35.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry, I was late.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.65,0:17:37.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dr. Becker!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.23,0:17:39.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why are you late when you're \N supposed to be on duty?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.61,0:17:42.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We'll do a full frontal craniotomy on both sides...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.74,0:17:44.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...remove the bone fragments...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.11,0:17:46.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...and damaged brain matter as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.36,0:17:48.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We'll then carefully remove the bullet...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.70,0:17:50.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...and finally, repair the artery.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.54,0:17:55.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This operation will take time, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.71,0:17:57.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone, let's give it our best!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.96,0:18:00.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Blood pressure, 120/80.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.88,0:18:02.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Pulse, 92.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.29,0:18:03.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Everything looks to be in good condition.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.92,0:18:05.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Anesthetics administered.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.51,0:18:15.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dr. Tenma!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.89,0:18:16.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.02,0:18:18.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This isn't your operation.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.64,0:18:21.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You must go to Operating Room #1 immediately.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.52,0:18:26.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Mayor, Mr. Roedecker, has collapsed \N from a cerebral thrombosis.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.40,0:18:30.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They're bringing him in by helicopter right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.57,0:18:33.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They should be arriving in ten minutes.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.11,0:18:36.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then please contact Dr. Boyer.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.78,0:18:39.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They're afraid that his artery may be blocked.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.24,0:18:41.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If that is the case, you must operate on him!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.83,0:18:47.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But I was about to start the operation on that child!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.04,0:18:52.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's an order from the director.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.09,0:19:00.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, this is Tenma.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.51,0:19:05.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, Tenma.  Please take care of the Mayor's case.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.18,0:19:08.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've already contacted Dr. Eisen and Dr. Boyer.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.77,0:19:10.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This situation should be acceptable, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.23,0:19:14.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But Director, I was about to start \N on another operation!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.86,0:19:17.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just leave that to Dr. Becker.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.07,0:19:21.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,W-With all due respect, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.03,0:19:23.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The patient in the operation I'm about to conduct...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.20,0:19:25.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...had a bullet graze the left side of his middle cerebral artery...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.78,0:19:28.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...and it'll be a very difficult operation!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.41,0:19:30.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,However, I'm confident that I can save him.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.66,0:19:34.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going to leave the Mayor's case to Dr. Boyer.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.29,0:19:37.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I must operate on the boy for him to survive.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.00,0:19:42.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, Tenma, please give everything \N you have to save the Mayor's life.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.42,0:19:46.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Mayor has already promised...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.17,0:19:52.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...to greatly increase our subsidy \N at the next medical assessment.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.10,0:19:55.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We can't have him die yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.89,0:19:59.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm counting on you, Tenma.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.31,0:20:01.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I expect a great deal from you.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.19,0:20:05.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, sir...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.98,0:20:11.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Mayor has arrived at the heliport!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.95,0:20:15.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Get to angio immediately after the CT.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.61,0:20:17.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please confirm which areas are blocked.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.12,0:20:27.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, you better make preparations, Dr. Tenma.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.25,0:20:30.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're relying on those brilliant skills of yours.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.05,0:20:38.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They think doctors are some kind of \N volunteers or something...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.59,0:20:44.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even before saving lives, we doctors \N value academics first.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.60,0:20:47.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't that right?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.06,0:20:52.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I merely operated on that opera singer \N like the director told me to.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.31,0:20:53.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It is not my fault.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.90,0:20:55.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.77,0:20:59.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Because people's lives aren't equal.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.32,0:21:04.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Give him back!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.82,0:21:08.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If only you had operated on him, he would have survived!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.08,0:21:16.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Give him back!  Give him back!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.92,0:21:21.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is wrong, Dr. Tenma?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.72,0:21:28.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.43,0:21:32.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I have an operation waiting for me in there.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.56,0:21:37.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,H-Hey, Dr. Tenma!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.98,0:21:40.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is an order from the director!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.14,0:21:42.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Mayor is currently having a CT scan done on him.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.85,0:21:45.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All doctors, please report to the trace-reading \N room immediately.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.06,0:21:45.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.19,0:21:48.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait, Dr. Tenma!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.15,0:21:49.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dr. Tenma!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.37,0:22:00.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You'll be okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.79,0:22:02.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hang in there!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.16,0:22:04.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll save you!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.39,0:22:21.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kill... him....
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.64,0:22:25.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kill... him....
